      "name": "FEA ensemble vs. experimental construct stiffness — primary QoI comparison",
      "description": "The FEA ensemble mean construct stiffness was 187.4 N/mm (SD 4.1 N/mm) against a reported experimental reference mean of 183.9 N/mm drawn from a companion cannulated-screw F1717 dataset collected under identical fixture and crosshead-speed settings. The normalized error metric E/uval = 0.94, satisfying the pre-established acceptance criterion of E/uval < 1.96. Percent difference was 1.9%, well within the 10% bound. No systematic bias was detected across the two participating laboratories. The result is therefore assessed as passing for construct stiffness."
