    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All three primary QoIs satisfy the pre-specified quantitative acceptance criteria (E/uval < 1.96; percent difference < 10%). Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed required levels. The single shortfall (Test conditions, achieved level 2 vs. required level 3) is accepted on the basis that quasi-static loading at 5 mm/min is the clinically relevant scenario and rate-dependence is negligible for Ti-6Al-4V under these conditions. Overall credibility evidence is assessed as sufficient to support the regulatory submission claim.",
